\begin{center}
{\large\textbf{Layer 2 --- Operating Model}} \\[6pt]
{\small Jonathan Erdmann \quad|\quad Last Updated: May 2026}
\end{center}

\vspace{8pt}

The living roadmap. Translates Layer 1 strategy into an executable, milestone-gated plan organized as a node hierarchy. Every element traces to a parent. Every initiative has a definition of done. Every phase has a gate condition, not just a timeline.

\textbf{Node hierarchy:} Breakthrough Goal $\rightarrow$ Annual Objective $\rightarrow$ Initiative $\rightarrow$ Action Item

\textbf{ID convention:} BG = Breakthrough Goal, AO = Annual Objective, IN = Initiative, AI = Action Item. Numbering restarts under each parent node.

\section{Phase Structure}

\textbf{Phase 1 --- Foundation and Credential} (2026--2027) \\
Gate: SMU EMBA complete; LinkedIn and resume rewritten for strategy positioning; internal visibility at Collins established with at least one executive sponsor identified.

\textbf{Phase 2 --- Positioning and Transition} (2027--2028) \\
Gate: Strategy-adjacent role or formal corporate strategy function secured within Collins at Senior Manager level or above.

\textbf{Phase 3 --- Perform and Credential for Corp Dev} (2028--2029) \\
Gate: At least one consequential strategic work product with traceable executive decision completed; M\&A adjacent exposure initiated.

\textbf{Phase 4 --- Advance and Optionality} (2029--2031) \\
Gate: Positioned credibly for corporate development role; CVC optionality assessed.

