\section{BG-02 --- Establish a Credible Professional Narrative and Targeted Network}

Success condition: the right people inside Collins and within the broader A\&D corporate strategy community know who you are, understand what you are building toward, and would surface your name when a relevant opportunity arises.

\subsection{AO-01 --- Complete LinkedIn and Resume Rewrite for Corporate Strategy Positioning (2026)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- LinkedIn Profile Rewrite}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Draft revised headline and about section using positioning thesis
  \item Reframe experience entries to surface strategic work products
  \item Build out skills section with strategy-relevant keywords
  \item Request two targeted recommendations --- one superior, one peer
  \item Schedule SMU Career Management Center profile review session
  \item Publish profile and establish baseline LinkedIn search appearance metric
  \item Track monthly search appearances filtered by corporate strategy and corporate development keywords; target consistent month-over-month growth
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-02 --- Resume Rewrite}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Schedule SMU Career Management Center resume review session
  \item Incorporate CMC feedback and finalize resume for corporate strategy targeting
  \item Tailor summary section to corporate strategy target function
\end{itemize}

\subsection{AO-02 --- Establish Internal Visibility at Collins and Identify Executive Sponsor (2027)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Build Executive Visibility within RTX}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Inform Kandyce of intent to reach out to Laura and confirm her awareness
  \item Reach out to Laura for a 20-minute informational interview on how she navigated the engineering-to-general-management transition at Collins
  \item Identify one or two additional internal Collins contacts through the Laura conversation
  \item Reach out to Amanda (RTX Talent) for a conversation on navigating the RTX ecosystem and making career planning efforts more robust
  \item Reconnect with Kathy (former RTX mentor, Director level) for a strategic conversation on the corporate strategy transition path
  \item Identify 2 to 3 additional senior leaders at Collins whose remit touches corporate strategy, business development, or general management
  \item Find credible contexts for engaging each --- program reviews, cross-functional initiatives, or direct conversations
  \item Prepare a clear and confident answer to the question ``what are you working toward?'' consistent with your positioning thesis
  \item Participate in at least one Collins-internal initiative with visibility above your current management chain
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-02 --- Secure Executive Sponsorship}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Based on visibility-building conversations, identify one senior leader with both organizational authority and genuine interest to advocate for your transition
  \item Make a direct and specific ask for periodic guidance and advocacy as you develop toward a strategy-adjacent role
  \item Establish a regular cadence of touchpoints --- quarterly at minimum --- to keep the sponsor informed of your progress
\end{itemize}

\subsection{AO-03 --- Build Targeted Network in Corporate Strategy at Large A\&D Primes (2026--2027)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- External Network Development at Large A\&D Primes}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Research corporate strategy and corporate development functions at L3Harris, Northrop Grumman, Lockheed Martin, and BAE Systems
  \item Identify 20+ specific individuals at Director level or above in target functions
  \item Build a simple contact tracking list with name, company, function, and connection status
  \item Send personalized connection requests with clear and credible context
  \item Convert 5+ connections into substantive conversations via call or informational interview
  \item Leverage SMU Cox alumni network specifically for A\&D strategy professionals
  \item Attend at least one A\&D industry event where corporate strategy professionals are present
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-02 --- LinkedIn Content and Professional Visibility}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Draft and publish 3 to 5 articles at the intersection of A\&D domain knowledge and strategic analysis
  \item Engage consistently with content from target contacts to build visibility before direct outreach
  \item Track engagement metrics on published content --- views, comments, shares
\end{itemize}

\section{BG-03 --- Transition into a Strategy-Adjacent Role at Collins Aerospace}

At the Senior Manager level or above. Collins is the first-move target. An external move to a large prime is the contingency if internal advancement stalls, assessed at the annual review.

\subsection{AO-01 --- Expand Current Role Scope to Include Strategy-Adjacent Activities (2026)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Sustain Baseline Performance in Current Engineering Management Role}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Maintain billable utilization at or above target for all three teams
  \item Document results with revenue impact framing for use in internal visibility conversations
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-02 --- Pursue Strategy-Adjacent Activities within Current Role}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Identify and volunteer for bids and proposals opportunities within Collins
  \item Contribute to at least one capture strategy or BD effort with visibility to senior leadership
  \item Identify other strategy-adjacent activities within current role scope --- program strategy, resource planning, make/buy analysis --- and actively pursue involvement
  \item Document contributions to strategy-adjacent work as part of internal positioning narrative
\end{itemize}

\subsection{AO-02 --- Pursue Strategy-Adjacent Scope or Role within Collins (2027)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Sustain Baseline Performance in Current Engineering Management Role}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Maintain billable utilization at or above target for all three teams
  \item Document results with revenue impact framing for use in internal visibility conversations
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-02 --- Continue and Deepen Strategy-Adjacent Activities within Current Role}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Build on BD and capture strategy involvement established in AO-01
  \item Expand scope of strategy-adjacent contributions --- seek ownership of a discrete strategic problem or initiative
  \item Document contributions as evidence for internal role transition conversations
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-03 --- Identify and Research Target Roles within Collins and RTX}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Map corporate strategy, business development, and general management roles within Collins and RTX at Senior Manager level or above
  \item Identify which business units and functions are most receptive to internal transitions from engineering management
  \item Track posted and anticipated openings in target functions
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-04 --- Build Relationships with Hiring Managers in Target Functions}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Leverage executive sponsorship and internal network to identify hiring managers in target functions
  \item Initiate conversations with hiring managers before roles are posted
  \item Position yourself as a known internal candidate through consistent visibility and direct relationship development
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-05 --- Execute Formal Application and Selection Process}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Apply to at least one internal Collins or RTX strategy-adjacent role when a credible opportunity is identified
  \item Use SMU CMC resources for internal mobility coaching and interview preparation
  \item Prepare and rehearse a clear and compelling narrative for internal interviews grounded in positioning thesis
\end{itemize}

\section{BG-04 --- Own a Consequential Strategic Work Product with Traceable Executive Decision}

Success condition: a market assessment, portfolio recommendation, competitive analysis, or strategic initiative where the link between the work and the decision is direct and attributable.

\subsection{AO-01 --- Deliver at Least One Consequential Strategic Work Product (2028--2029)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Identify and Own a High-Visibility Strategic Initiative}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Within first 90 days in a strategy-adjacent role, identify the highest-impact analytical or strategic problem available to own
  \item Propose ownership of the initiative to your manager with a clear framing of the problem, the analytical approach, and the expected output
  \item Deliver a structured work product --- market assessment, competitive analysis, portfolio recommendation, or strategic initiative --- with a clear recommendation and supporting logic
  \item Present findings to senior leadership and document the decision or action that resulted
\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{IN-02 --- Build a Personal Library of Strategic Work Products}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Maintain a running record of strategic analyses, frameworks, and recommendations produced in role
  \item Ensure each work product is documented with the decision it informed and the outcome that followed
  \item Use this library as the evidence base for future positioning conversations and career reviews
\end{itemize}

\subsection{AO-02 --- Develop M\&A Adjacent Exposure (2029)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Build M\&A Process Knowledge and Exposure}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Identify internal transaction support, partnership structuring, or build/buy/partner analysis opportunities within Collins or RTX
  \item Volunteer to support at least one M\&A adjacent process --- due diligence, integration planning, or strategic partnership evaluation
  \item Complete at least one structured M\&A or corporate development course or certification to formalize process knowledge
\end{itemize}

\section{BG-05 --- Be Positioned Credibly for a Corporate Development Role at a Large A\&D Prime}

With M\&A adjacent exposure and financial modeling depth sufficient to compete as a serious candidate. Directional objectives to be refined at Phase 3 annual review.

\subsection{AO-01 --- Develop Financial Modeling Depth Sufficient for Corporate Development (2029--2030)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Build Applied Financial Modeling Capability}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Apply Valuation and Analysis and Corporate Financial Policies coursework from EMBA in a professional context
  \item Identify opportunities within strategy role to build and present financial models --- business cases, investment analyses, portfolio valuations
  \item Complete at least one external financial modeling course or certification beyond the EMBA --- candidates include CFA Level 1 or a dedicated financial modeling program
  \item Develop fluency with M\&A valuation methodologies --- DCF, comparable company analysis, precedent transactions
\end{itemize}

\subsection{AO-02 --- Position Credibly for a Corporate Development Role (2030--2031)}

\subsubsection{IN-01 --- Build Corporate Development Market Presence and Candidacy}

\begin{itemize}
  \item Identify and research corporate development functions and active practitioners at RTX, L3Harris, Northrop Grumman, and Lockheed Martin
  \item Develop relationships specifically within corporate development functions at large primes --- distinct from the broader strategy network
  \item Assess internal RTX corporate development opportunities as a first-move option given existing relationships
  \item Prepare a corporate development-specific positioning narrative grounded in strategy credentials, M\&A exposure, and financial modeling depth
  \item Target at least one corporate development role application with a complete and compelling candidacy
\end{itemize}

